##"thousands of miles in reverse" to deliver food to Hubei: Police officers on duty do not shake hands, the driver said, "This trip is worth it! " | photo story

Wechat Bqshenyidu

Features, Beijing Youth Daily, the official public number

Reporter / Li Dong

Editor / Edward Shek, Jianhua Song

It was a fast-assembling convoy of 10 trucks and 12 drivers. It took 26 hours and 1,000 km to transport 300 tonnes of vegetables from Handan to Red Cliff at noon on the 9th.

As of 6:00 on February 12,44404 cases of NCP had been confirmed in China, including 33366 cases in Hubei. After the traffic control in Hubei Province, the supply of living materials became an important link to win the battle.

As of 12:00 on February 1, Hubei Province has received a cumulative donation of 6.91 billion yuan, 10.02 million pieces of various materials. Behind the numbers are hundreds of truckers traveling thousands of miles in reverse from all over the country.

Han Zhiping was an ordinary truck driver, speaking a thick dialect of Handan. On February 8, he, as captain, led a dozen "card friends" from Handan, Hebei "Turnip Cabbage" to the dinner table of Red Cliff people.

Beiqingshen once reporters followed the convoy day and night, recording the entire process of the delivery of relief supplies to Hubei.

01

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At 8 am on February 8,10 lorries loaded with vegetables such as white turnips, winter melons and tomatoes set off from Yongnian County to Red Cliff.

The vegetable donor, Song Furu, a local businessman from Handan, learned of the severity of the disease and the shortage of supplies in the province. He bought 300 tons of vegetables from market farmers and made a targeted donation to residents of Red Cliff.

Song Furu in the freight platform issued an emergency summoned drivers to Hubei Delivery of materials, including Han Zhiping, 12 large freight drivers quickly assembled to form a fleet.

It took 20 stevedores a day and a half to fill 10 lorries with 300 tons of vegetables.

02

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Affected by the fog, 10 large trucks set out soon, was stopped at the entrance of the highway. While waiting, the driver, Takashi Musashi, Rehung the fallen banner.

Musashi Jie wechat named "national freight" , 12 drivers, he was the loudest, almost shouting words. "The whole country is fighting the epidemic, we should also contribute! " He said he graduated from Primary School, I don't know, but that's what he meant.

By midday on February 8th, 10 lorries were at last on the highway, speeding along.

03

In the motorcade, Bow Shuai flies the fastest, all the way in the motorcade front, in the walkie-talkie, everybody jokes to call him "the small plane" .

"small plane" is 90, this time out of the family, hope that the report does not write his real name. He had driven to Laos to transport bananas from abroad to his home country, and he wanted to leave his footprint across the country. He claimed to have seen "the big picture" when he was trucking relief tents to Jiuzhaigou Valley during the earthquake. "small plane" said that the delivery of this batch of vegetables is the most urgent, "you know what it is like to have nothing to eat? " He said, he had such a transport experience.

04

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The team on the highway for more than three hours, Captain Han Zhiping car alarm, he had to stop the car to check. Han Zhiping, a 45-year-old driver with a 20-year driving history, checks his car carefully before he sets off.

Along the way, Han Zhiping "nagging" did not stop, a reminder "slow, the night arrived also can not unload" , and a shout "do not run fast, 80 Km / h the most fuel-efficient. He stayed at the back of the line so that he could go to the rescue in case the front car broke down.

At 10 p.m. on Feb. 8, the convoy drove more than 600 kilometers to a rest stop at the Soul Mountain Service area near the border with Hubei Province.

05

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At 10:30 p.m. , Li Longfei set up a gas stove in his car to cook noodles, complete with instant noodles seasoning and cabbage leaves.

Li Long has been running the bus for more than 7 years, his wife is a "Karsao" , because the transport has the risk of infection, he did not let his wife with the car. To reassure his wife, he prepared a face mask for himself before he left.

Li Longfei said that this trip to Hubei is not a loss-making sports car, vegetable donors to provide drivers with gas mileage car subsidies. "Some things, do not do will regret a lifetime. ". Li Longfei said as he ate, his face thick, in the service area after dinner, he began to call his daughter-in-law to report the trip.

06

The driver, Li Yongjun, 47, a big brother in the motorcade, took care of a busload of winter melons.

Before departure, the family reminded Li Yongjun Hubei May rain, for fear of winter melon was wet will rot, he specially bought a new plastic sheet will cover the car. After a section of the road is being repaired, Li Yongjun deliberately slowed down the speed of the car, for fear of melon is bad.

After eating a bowl of instant noodles in the Soul Mountain Service area, Li Yongjun picked up his mobile phone to check the weather, only to find that it would rain the day after tomorrow.

07

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wang Haiqing, a native of Inner Mongolia, was the only mainlander in the convoy. On the seventh day of the Lunar New Year, he shipped goods from his hometown to Beijing and finally to Yongnian County, Handan.

Arriving in Handan just in time for the vegetable donors to recruit transport drivers, he joined the convoy without a word.

The epidemic prevention situation is grim. According to him, the villages in his hometown in Inner Mongolia have not allowed villagers to go in and out at will. On this trip to Hubei, his family was very worried. After he made a safe phone call to his family, he just lay down in the car and went to sleep.

We agreed to continue on February 9 at 4:00 a.m.

08

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Zhou Hongtao and Feng Cuihua are a couple. The couple signed up without hesitation when they saw the news of the shipment.

They bought a case of instant noodles in case there was no food to eat on the way. "really no food, we have a car load of cabbages LE, " the couple joked.

For the first time in years, the husband and wife were out running cars to deliver relief supplies. On the way, they looked through the mobile phone news, learned that the Hubei Epidemic Emergency, Feng Cuihua more feel this trip "worth! "

While resting in the Soul Mountain Service area, two truck drivers who had taken noodles to Wuhan also rested there. Only after chatting did it become clear that the place for unloading noodles was very close to the Huoshenshan hospital. Before leaving, both sides said to take care of each other.

09

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At 4:00 a.m. on February 9th, a departure signal came over the intercom.

At 6 o'clock, they entered Wuhan. The drivers put on face masks. Walkie-talkies came from the Captain Han Zhiping Tips, "pay attention to protection, we do not open the window. "

At 8:30 am, the motorcade arrived at the West exit of Wushen Expressway. The epidemic prevention personnel on duty disinfected each vehicle one by one.

10

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At Red Cliff West highway, 12 drivers of the convoy were given two-day vehicle passes after submitting documents, taking temperature measurements and registering.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The man on duty warned the truck driver, Hou Xuliang, that the pass had clearly marked the passage time and that the vehicle had to leave Red Cliff within the stipulated time. If you exceed the time limit, it will affect the traffic.

"thank you very much for your support to Red Cliff. We will not shake hands for security reasons. " . The police on duty, epidemic prevention workers remind drivers must wash hands frequently, wear masks.

11

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At noon on February 9, the convoy and the Chibi Civil Affairs Bureau completed the handover of donated materials. To the material transfer area, Han Zhiping learned that the day before the arrival of materials, there are a number of units to organize free food, including hospitals, welfare institutions, functional units canteen.

At the time of unloading, the Red Cliff's local epidemic prevention department issued drivers and vehicles with documents and passes to transport supplies. With this certificate, you can avoid the toll of the round-trip highway.
